The paper proposes a new change detection algorithm for multi-temporal remote sensing images using deep networks and slow feature analysis. The paper involves image processing, feature extraction, and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for feature mapping and threshold algorithms, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for deep network modeling, and neural networks (cs.NE) for feature extraction. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
